*   [ ] **Database Schema Setup (MySQL/Hostinger):**
    *   Create table `wp_revenue_audit_data`.
    *   **Columns:** `user_id`, `audit_date`, `raw_score_awareness`, `raw_score_consideration` (etc. for all 5 stages), `total_score`, `architect_notes` (text field for your human input), `subscription_status` (active/inactive).
*   [ ] **Authentication System:**
    *   Build **Magic Link** login system (Passwordless PHP flow).
    *   Create session handling: If user clicks link -> verify token -> set secure cookie.
*   [ ] **Webhook Listener (The Bridge):**
    *   Set up an endpoint (e.g., `richardnorwood.com/api/rjat-listener.php`) to receive JSON payloads from the RJAT form tool via n8n.
